  "derivation_layer": {
    "source_latex": "% BEGIN TZP DERIVATION LAYER\n\\tzpsection{Derivation Layer}\n\\paragraph{Primary Equation.}\n\\begin{equation}\n\\Box_T\\phi\n=\ng^{ab}\n\\nabla^{T}_{a}\n\\nabla^{T}_{b}\n\\phi .\n\\end{equation}\n\n\\paragraph{Primary Derivation.}\nThe ordinary d'Alembertian is the metric contraction of two covariant derivatives acting on a field.  \nIn Trawinistic geometry, replace the ordinary covariant derivative with $\\nabla^T$:\n\n\\begin{equation}\n\\nabla_a\\nabla_b\\phi\n\\quad\\longrightarrow\\quad\n\\nabla^T_a\\nabla^T_b\\phi .\n\\end{equation}\n\nThen contract using the regularized inverse metric $g^{ab}$:\n\n\\begin{equation}\n\\Box_T\\phi\n=\ng^{ab}\n\\nabla^{T}_{a}\n\\nabla^{T}_{b}\n\\phi .\n\\end{equation}\n\n\\paragraph{Interpretation.}\n$\\Box_T$ extends wave propagation and field equations into the Trawinistic manifold by replacing ordinary derivatives with TZP-compatible covariant derivatives.\n% END TZP DERIVATION LAYER"
  },
